{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/shopify-fix-leverage-browser-caching","result":{"pageContext":{"id":143,"date":"2020-12-07T10:25:38","date_gmt":"2020-12-07T10:25:38","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=143"},"modified":"2021-01-01T02:35:53","modified_gmt":"2021-01-01T02:35:53","slug":"shopify-fix-leverage-browser-caching","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/shopify-fix-leverage-browser-caching/","title":{"rendered":"Shopify: Fix leverage Browser caching"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Whether you&#8217;re a merchant or a developer, you&#8217;re likely an avid for speed optimization &#8211; after all it is one of the not so mere details that do play an important role on any website, especially the e-commerce ones.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Although Shopify does not allow any customization to be done on the server, you can still leverage browser caching on the client-side, within your theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adding the code to your theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>In your Shopify Admin go to&nbsp;<strong>online store &gt; themes &gt; actions &gt; edit code</strong></li><li>&nbsp;In your&nbsp;<strong>theme.liquid file</strong>, find the&nbsp;<em>&lt;head&gt;</em>&nbsp;<em>(press CTRL + F or command + F on Mac)</em></li><li>paste this code right below the&nbsp;<em>&lt;head&gt;</em>&nbsp;tag:<br><strong><code> &lt;meta http-equiv=\"Expires\" content=\"30\" /&gt; </code> </strong></li><li>Save.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>That is it! The meta data above means that document is considered expired after the specified date and time. If you set it to “0“, the browser will check for a fresh new document on each visit, which can potentially add some extra loading time to your website.</p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Improve your website&#8217;s performance by leveraging the browser&#8217;s cache.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":150,"comment_status":"open","